miscConds.notes: Restitution to be distributed in the following manner - $651.23 to the Plainfield Travel Plaza and $204.20 to the Royal Supermarket. Restitution to be repaid in monthly increments of no less than $50 starting May 1, 2016. In the event that the Defendant is revoked or discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the Court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement action will be used to collect the debt.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment or maintaining any open checking accounts.  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

15CF170 & 16CM3 Cases called @ 1:52 p.m. Defendant Tracey J. Loucks in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Tracey J. Loucks in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. As to both cases: Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. Defendant will be represented by SPD. 16CM3: NGP entered as to all counts. DA Blader requesting a $300 Cash Bond. Atty Szilagyi requesting a Sig Bond. The parties could possibly resolve the matter if given the time to discuss the matter. Recess for the parties to talk.   

Case recalled @ 2:31 p.m.  The parties have reached a resolution. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Upon motion of the State the Court amends Cts 2 & 4 to Misdemeanor Bail Jumping contrary to Wis Stat 946.49(1)(a).  Plea: Cts 1 - 4 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 16CM3 - DRI. Statement by DE. Court orders: S/W - 2 years probation - Conditions:   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, AODA and follow through, Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment or maintaining any open checking accounts, Restitution in the amount of $855.43 to be distributed as follows - $651.23 to the Plainfield Travel Plaza and $204.20 to the Royal Supermarket in Plainfield, Restitution to be repaid in monthly increments of no less than $50 starting May 1, 2016, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.
Body Only with Extradition Within the Continental United States

Case Called @ 2:05 PM: Defendant Tracey J. Loucks not in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In light of nonappearance, Arrest Warrant authorized with Extradition within the Continental US.    Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.
